						<summary>

						<p>This is fragmentary. It records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">Śrī yakki-paḻañjalāgai-achchu</hi> to the temple by Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-Śilaśeṭṭi. Close to this is another fragment (of a Pāṇḍya king) dated in the 9th year and mentioning the temple of Māndaranīsuram-Uḍaiyār and the village Pulariyūr.</p>						

						</summary>
